Congratulations to newly inducted members of the East Campus Maurie Taylor Chapter of the National Honor Society.
New members are: Kole Christoff, Evelyn Corona, Katrina Cronin, Sarina Dale, Alyssa Exon, Alexandra Fogleman, Jillian Galuszka, Makayla Hazlett, Lissette Hernandez, Malory Karasek, Skyler Kunetka, Kara Lard, Jessica Letmanski, Jocelyn Salazar, Alexis Schwartz.
The ceremony was held Aug. 12 at Veteran's Park, and conducted by Brent Anderlik, Paige Bantner, Annie Bantner, Sandra Ruiz, and Stormy Mosson, along with sponsor Mrs. K. Freiberger.

The East Campus strength facility also got some new additions as part of the plan to offer strength to freshmen in the future.
We're looking forward to getting students back in the buildings!

post_text: Last week, more than 80 MCHS staff members came together for a series of 3-hour "Focus on the Future" Digital Learning Bootcamp planning sessions. These events, led by our five amazing Digital Literacy Coaches, provided collaborative planning time for educators as they find new and creative ways to engage students with synchronous digital lessons. MCHS looks forward to being back in class with our students!

post_text: The health and safety of our students and staff is a major priority. MCHS has been acquiring PPE and sanitation supplies and equipment all summer long. Wipes, sanitizing supplies and stations in classrooms and hallways, temperature devices and kiosks, acrylic barriers, and parent and staff daily health certifications will be part of the new normal. More specific details will be forth coming in the next several weeks. Our focus has been striking a balance between health and safety and in-person learning. We will continue to work tirelessly towards this goal. We appreciate all the feedback. Thank you!

post_text: Such a great story! Congratulations to SSG Speciale!
shared_text:
McHenry Strength is with Kennon Speciale.
June 19 at 12:50 PM ·

Received a picture last night! Made my day!!

Back in 2013, a young man named Kenny Speciale worked hard in the weight room and loved training! He had a goal of being in the Marines. I went back and found a picture in some files of the day his older friends returned to visit in their uniforms. Yesterday, this same young man sends me a picture after graduating as a Staff Sergeant Drill Instructor! Inspirational to see what our students can accomplish & work toward their goals!!

We are so proud of you SSG Speciale Kennon Speciale!💪🇺🇸 SSG Speciale has continued to make personal fitness a priority in his life and has earned 6 different personal training certifications since graduating. GO WARRIORS!!!

#WarriorPride156 #Marines

McHenry Community High School District #156
